{#-
  HoverCard — Popover variant opened by hover (with delay) for visual
  previews. Composes the `popover` controller (positioning + animation +
  Esc/click-outside dismiss) and the `hover-card` controller (mouseenter
  / mouseleave triggers with delays).

  Reuses Tooltip's 400 ms open delay via inline timing, NO new motion token.
  Close delay 200 ms (anti-flash on fast pointer movement). HoverCard is a
  *visual preview* surface — does NOT open on focus (≠ Tooltip). Esc still
  dismisses.

  Use HoverCard for: user mention previews (avatar + name + role + bio),
  link previews (favicon + title + summary), tag previews (description).

  Use Tooltip (Ring 1) for: short descriptive text on icon-only buttons.
  Use Popover (Ring 2) for: click-to-open contextual surfaces with action.

  Touch behavior: HoverCard is desktop-first. On touch (no hover), the
  card effectively doesn't open. For touch-friendly preview surfaces, use
  Popover or DropdownMenu instead.

  Parameters:
    htmlId       (string, optional) — auto-generated. Stamped on content
                                      for aria-controls chaining.
    placement    (string, optional) — Floating UI placement. Default 'top'
                                      (HoverCard convention — preview
                                      sits above the inline trigger).
    offset       (int, optional)    — gap from trigger in px (default 8).
    openDelay    (int, optional)    — ms before open (default 400).
    closeDelay   (int, optional)    — ms before close (default 200).
    open         (bool, optional)   — false (default). SSR-open hover cards.
    className    (string, optional) — extra classes on the wrap.

  Blocks:
    trigger (required) — the inline element the user hovers over. Typically
                         an inline `<a>` (mention link), `<span>` with
                         tabindex (preview anchor), or an avatar. Consumer
                         stamps `data-popover-target="trigger"`,
                         `aria-haspopup="dialog"`, `aria-expanded` (false),
                         `aria-controls="{{ hoverCardHtmlId }}"`.
    content (required) — the preview surface body. Composes Card-style
                         envelope (avatar + heading + paragraph + actions).
                         Consumer-provided HTML.
-#}

{%- set htmlId     = htmlId     | default('cremona-hover-card-' ~ random()) -%}
{%- set placement  = placement  | default('top') -%}
{%- set offset     = offset     | default(8) -%}
{%- set openDelay  = openDelay  | default(400) -%}
{%- set closeDelay = closeDelay | default(200) -%}
{%- set open       = open       | default(false) -%}
{%- set className  = className  | default('') -%}

{%- set _classes = ['cremona-popover', 'cremona-hover-card'] -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

{%- set hoverCardHtmlId = htmlId -%}

<div
  class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}"
  data-controller="popover hover-card"
  data-action="mouseenter->hover-card#enter mouseleave->hover-card#leave keydown.esc@window->popover#close"
  data-popover-placement-value="{{ placement }}"
  data-popover-offset-value="{{ offset }}"
  data-popover-open-value="{{ open ? 'true' : 'false' }}"
  data-hover-card-open-delay-value="{{ openDelay }}"
  data-hover-card-close-delay-value="{{ closeDelay }}"
>
  {%- block trigger -%}{%- endblock -%}
  <div
    id="{{ htmlId }}"
    class="cremona-popover__content cremona-hover-card__content"
    data-popover-target="content"
    data-state="{{ open ? 'open' : 'closed' }}"
    data-placement="{{ placement }}"
    role="dialog"
    {{ open ? '' : 'hidden' }}
  >
    {%- block content -%}{%- endblock -%}
  </div>
</div>
